《[[太陽報_(英國)|太陽報]]》称一些场面是「可耻的」，并悲伤地写到“在伦敦奥运会即将在一年内开幕的时间里，我们的名誉在这个最糟糕的时刻受到了严重的破坏”，“这是绝对的混乱状态，它对生命和财产来说是严重的威胁”<ref>{{cite article |title=Be decisive |url=http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/news/sun_says/244723/The-Sun-Says.html |work=[[The_Sun_(United_Kingdom)|The Sun]] |date=2011-08-09 |accessdate=2011-08-09 |archive-date=2009-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090522103135/http://www.thesun.co.uk/sol/homepage/news/sun_says/244723/The-Sun-Says.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

《[[每日电讯报|每日电讯报]]》的主编说道“我们在伦敦和各地自周六夜晚以来所经历过的事件呈现出一个全新的现象：暴力无秩序行为仅仅只为犯罪……在如此的环境下，如果法律救济为的是保护大多数人的利益的话，那么我们也仅仅只有一个反应——暴徒必须被告戒他们必须尊重国家的法律”<ref>{{cite article |title=The criminals who shame our nation |url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/telegraph-view/8691352/The-criminals-who-shame-our-nation.html |work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] |date=2011-08-09 |accessdate=2011-08-09 |archive-date=2020-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201017091438/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/comment/telegraph-view/8691352/The-criminals-who-shame-our-nation.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

《[[卫报|卫报]]》呼吁公众支持警察：“……2011英格蘭骚乱成为了无秩序与有秩序之间的一种竞赛。在这个竞赛中有一个重要的附加说明——两边只有一个是对的。暴力袭击、破坏必须停止，[[法治|法治]]不是唯一保护自己对抗非法破坏的工具，但是法律必须得到执行”<ref>{{cite article |title=Urban riots: The battle for the streets |url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2011/aug/09/urban-riots-battle-streets-editorial |work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]] |date=2011-08-09 |accessdate=2011-08-09 |archive-date=2012-09-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120919213428/http://www.guardian.co.uk/commentisfree/2011/aug/09/urban-riots-battle-streets-editorial |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

一些记者把这起骚乱与[[2005年法国骚乱|2005年法国骚乱]]相比较<ref name="nytimes1">{{cite web |author=By J. David Goodman |url=http://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/08/09/plus-ca-change-riots-in-london-and-paris/ |title=Riots in London and Paris: Plus Ça Change? - NYTimes.com |location=France;Great Britain |publisher=Thelede.blogs.nytimes.com |date=2006-11-17 |accessdate=2011-08-11 |archive-date=2020-08-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200817203553/https://thelede.blogs.nytimes.com/2011/08/09/plus-ca-change-riots-in-london-and-paris/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=10744251 |title=UK riots parallel France - World - NZ Herald News |publisher=Nzherald.co.nz |date=2011-03-17 |accessdate=2011-08-11 |archive-date=2011-08-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110811064838/http://www.nzherald.co.nz/world/news/article.cfm?c_id=2&objectid=10744251 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，因为两起事件都因外裔的年轻人在与警察的冲突中死亡而引发<ref name="nytimes1"/>。

=== 公众 ===
许多民众呼吁政府让警察使用英国以外的制止骚乱的方法，比如使用[[水炮|水炮]]和[[橡皮子弹|橡皮子弹]]等，而这些方法以前都被英国高官拒绝<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/8690220/London-riots-send-in-water-cannon-to-clear-streets-Theresa-May-told.html|title=London riots: send in water cannon to clear streets, Theresa May told|author=Tom Whitehead, and Andrew Hough|date=2011-08-08|work=The Daily Telegraph|accessdate=2011-08-10|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128084329/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/8690220/London-riots-send-in-water-cannon-to-clear-streets-Theresa-May-told.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=CapitalFM>{{cite news |title=Kenyans take shelter from London riots |newspaper=Capital FM News, Kenya |date=2011-08-09 |url=http://www.capitalfm.co.ke/news/2011/08/09/kenyans-take-shelter-from-london-riots/ |accessdate=2011-08-10 |archive-date=2019-08-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190822094351/https://www.capitalfm.co.ke/news/2011/08/kenyans-take-shelter-from-london-riots/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Siddique|first=Haroon|title=Theresa May urged to send in water cannon to tackle riots|url=http://www.guardian.co.uk/uk/2011/aug/09/theresa-may-water-cannon-riots|newspaper=The Guardian|date=2011-08-09|accessdate=2011-08-10|archive-date=2013-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130627000239/http://www.guardian.co.uk/uk/2011/aug/09/theresa-may-water-cannon-riots|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

上万名使用社交网站的英国民众帮助受破坏的街道和商户从事清理工作。如民众利用[[Twitter|Twitter]]和[[Facebook|Facebook]]来报道骚乱的相关讯息，以让那些志愿者方便展开清理工作<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://londonist.com/2011/08/wombles-needed-how-to-help-with-the-riot-cleanup.php |title=Wombles Needed: How To Help With The Riot Cleanup |publisher=Londonist |date=2010-08-11 |accessdate=2011-08-09 |archive-date=2011-11-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111116214159/http://londonist.com/2011/08/wombles-needed-how-to-help-with-the-riot-cleanup.php |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-14456857 |title=BBC News - Twitter and Facebook users arrange London riot clean-up |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2011-08-09 |archive-date=2020-12-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201207014303/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-14456857 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/bb2c434a-c263-11e0-9ede-00144feabdc0.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2011-08-10 |archive-date=2012-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120506225950/http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/bb2c434a-c263-11e0-9ede-00144feabdc0.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。在[[克拉彭|克拉彭]]（''Clapham''）交界处，许多志愿者拿着扫帚清扫路面<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.sky.com/home/uk-news/article/16046412|title=Locals Co-ordinate Riot Clean-Up Squads|publisher=Sky|accessdate=2011-08-10|archive-date=2012-02-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120211012951/http://news.sky.com/home/uk-news/article/16046412|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在[[Facebook|Facebook]]上，有超过9万人加入了一个名为“支持警察反对伦敦骚乱者”（Supporting the Met Police against the London rioters）的组织<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.facebook.com/pages/Supporting-the-Met-Police-against-the-London-rioters/152937041453243 |title=Supporting the Met Police against the London rioters |publisher=Facebook |date= |accessdate=2011-08-10 |archive-date=2012-12-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121213043038/http://www.facebook.com/pages/Supporting-the-Met-Police-against-the-London-rioters/152937041453243 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

由于许多掠夺者在掠夺商店、体育用品店等商户的商品时并没有蒙面，甚至有的还摆出姿势被相机照了下来，所以一些民众已经将不少犯罪者的照片贴在了社交网站上<ref name="Tom de Castella & Caroline McClatchey">{{cite web | url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-14463452 | title=UK riots: What turns people into looters? | accessdate=2011-08-10 | archive-date=2020-11-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112034918/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/magazine-14463452 | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.ifeng.com/world/special/lundunsaoluan/content-3/detail_2011_08/12/8357478_0.shtml |title=英民众网上人肉搜索抓骚乱暴徒 效率远高于警方 |accessdate=2011-08-12 |archive-date=2019-09-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190909085404/http://news.ifeng.com/world/special/lundunsaoluan/content-3/detail_2011_08/12/8357478_0.shtml |dead-url=no }}</ref>。8月10日，大清洁团队在暴乱后的晚上进入克拉彭镇，以展示民众的团结与自尊<ref>{{cite web |author=now to post a comment! |url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bp_HsHrJb4A&feature=player_embedded |title=London riots: The big community clean up in Clapham after night of looting and violence |publisher=YouTube |date= |accessdate=2011-08-11 |archive-date=2016-03-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160316160322/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bp_HsHrJb4A&feature=player_embedded |dead-url=no }}</ref>。10日八点，''[[Jeremy_Myers|Jeremy Myers]]''使用Twitter来调动志愿者去清理'''Piccadilly Gardens'''（伦敦繁华的大街之一）和[[皮卡迪利圓環|皮卡迪利圓環]]（伦敦繁华的大街之一）。[[曼彻斯特|曼彻斯特]]市商业区的职员和[[曼彻斯特大学|曼彻斯特大学]]的成员都加入了志愿者队伍，而食物店则免费提供饮料和小吃<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-manchester-14478902|title=Hundreds join Manchester clean-up after riots|publisher=BBC|accessdate=2011-08-12|archive-date=2020-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123183301/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-manchester-14478902|dead-url=no}}</ref>，该市议员兼市议会发言人''Pat Karney''说：“今天真实的曼彻斯特人的精神已经充分地体现了出来”。

8月8日，一名来自哈克尼區的黑人妇女在发生骚乱后的路边痛骂骚乱者的画面被《每日电讯报》的记者用手机录了下来，该视频名为“[[2011年英国骚乱|Heroine of Hackney]]”已经在网络上非常流行<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.seek4media.com/video/14899-pauline_pearce_the_heroine_of_hackney_takes_on_the_rioters.html |title=视频观看地址 |accessdate=2011-08-12 |archive-date=2018-12-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181212143054/https://www.seek4media.com/video/14899-pauline_pearce_the_heroine_of_hackney_takes_on_the_rioters.html |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Gardham|first=Duncan|title='Hackney speech woman' revealed to be local jazz singer|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/8692712/Hackney-speech-woman-revealed-to-be-local-jazz-singer.html|newspaper=Telegraph|date=2011-08-10|accessdate=2011-08-12|archive-date=2020-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201128084342/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/8692712/Hackney-speech-woman-revealed-to-be-local-jazz-singer.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name='fearless hackney woman evening standard'>{{cite news | first = Tom | last = Harper | title = A million hits for footage of Hackney woman berating looters | date = 2011-08-09 | url = http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/standard/article-23976731-a-million-hits-for-footage-of-hackney-woman-berating-looters.do | work = [[Evening_Standard|Evening Standard]] | accessdate = 2011-08-10 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://archive.is/20130114051727/http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/standard/article-23976731-a-million-hits-for-footage-of-hackney-woman-berating-looters.do | archivedate = 2013-01-14 }}</ref><ref name='fearless hackney woman telegraph'> {{cite news | title = London riots: Woman confronts rioters in Hackney | date = 2011-08-09 | url = http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/8690275/London-riots-Woman-confronts-rioters-in-Hackney.html | work = [[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]] | accessdate = 2011-08-10}}</ref>。

11日，旨在让公众更多参与政治的英国政府开设的电子请愿网上，有关惩罚骚乱者的联署信已经有超过10万人签名，达到了提交给议会审议的要求。这份请愿书在短短的几天时间内吸引了众多人签名，请愿书呼吁剥夺那些因本次骚乱被判罪的人所享有的国家[[福利|福利]]。不过即使这一请愿提交给议会讨论也未必能获得通过成为法律<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://news.ifeng.com/world/special/lundunsaoluan/content-3/detail_2011_08/12/8355175_0.shtml?_from_ralated |title=英国超10万民众网上请愿取缔暴民国家福利 |accessdate=2011-08-12 |archive-date=2019-09-10 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190910213211/http://news.ifeng.com/world/special/lundunsaoluan/content-3/detail_2011_08/12/8355175_0.shtml?_from_ralated |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

